80. Build a test cookie with the setcookie( ) function using PHP.
code:
<?php
// Set a test cookie named "TestCookie" with value "HelloWorld"
// Cookie expires in 1 hour (3600 seconds) and is available across the whole domain
setcookie("TestCookie", "HelloWorld", time() + 3600, "/");

// Display message
echo "<h3>Test Cookie Example</h3>";

// Check if cookie is set
if(isset($_COOKIE['TestCookie'])) {
    echo "Cookie 'TestCookie' is set! Value: " . $_COOKIE['TestCookie'];
} else {
    echo "Cookie 'TestCookie' is not set yet. Please refresh the page.";
}
?>
